2.Command to schedule a system shutdown in 10 minutes

syntax:shutdown-h+10
This command schedules a system shutdown in 10 minutes and sent a message to users logged to indicate
command:$sudo shutdown-h+10

3.comand to immediateltart the computer

syntax:shutdown -r now
It will immediately restarts the computer without any delay
command:$sudo shutdown -r now

4.Comand to create a delayed reboot with 5 minutes delay

syntax:shutdown-r+5
It schedule for restart computer with 5 minutes delay and send message to user logged
comand:sudo shutdown-r+5

5,6.To check scheduled shutdown and cancel shutdown

syntax:shutdown-c
It checks for any scheduled system shutdowns and also cancels then if there cancellation of shutdown
command:$sudo shutdown-c

7.command to use the emergency reboot comand to forcefully restart the system.

syntax:reboot-f
It forcefully restarts the system without properly terminating process.It result in data loss or system instability.
It should used when systems in critical state.
command:$sdo reboot-f

